                  , and employed and entrusted by him to receive money and notes for and on account of his said master, and being such servant, so employed, and entrusted by virtue of such employment, received and took into his possession, four three-shilling bank tokens, and one one-pound bank note, for and on account of his said master, and that he did afterwards feloniously embezzle, secrete, and steal the said three-shilling pieces, the monies of the said 
                     <persName id="t18160214-55-person635">
                        Charles 
                        Richard Constantine Gould
                     <interp inst="t18160214-55-person635" type="surname" value="Richard Constantine Gould"></interp>
